ation, Tatjana Schoenmaker. The 20-year-old took the games by storm â€” or, rather, made waves in the pool â€” as she ascended to the upper echelons of South Africa's swimming sorority. She outshone world stars Chad le Clos and Cameron van der Burgh after winning back-to-back golds. Schoenmaker is definitely the new cover girl of SA swimming. She won two gold medals, in the women's 100m and 200m breaststroke, smashing the African records for both, the latter with a time of 2:22.02.   Halala to all the SA queens!